    "explanation": "Cryptography protects information through mathematical transformation. Symmetric encryption (AES) uses one shared key for both encryption and decryption \u2014 fast but requires secure key exchange. Asymmetric encryption (RSA) uses public/private key pairs \u2014 anyone can encrypt with the public key, only the private key decrypts. Hash functions (SHA-256) produce fixed-size fingerprints \u2014 any change in input completely changes the output. Digital signatures combine hashing with asymmetric encryption for authentication and integrity.",
